    summary:
      'Curried Cauliflower Gratin could be just the <b>lacto ovo vegetarian</b> recipe you\'ve been looking for. One serving contains <b>313 calories</b>, <b>6g of protein</b>, and <b>26g of fat</b>. This recipe serves 6 and costs $1.59 per serving. It works well as a rather cheap side dish. If you have butter, curry powder, cauliflower, and a few other ingredients on hand, you can make it. It is brought to you by Foodista. This recipe is liked by 8 foodies and cooks. From preparation to the plate, this recipe takes about <b>45 minutes</b>. With a spoonacular <b>score of 53%</b>, this dish is pretty good. Similar recipes include <a href="https://spoonacular.com/recipes/curried-cabbage-kale-gratin-641060">Curried Cabbage & Kale Gratin</a>, <a href="https://spoonacular.com/recipes/curried-sweet-potato-gratin-172592">Curried Sweet Potato Gratin</a>, and <a href="https://spoonacular.com/recipes/curried-cabbage-kale-gratin-1349369">Curried Cabbage & Kale Gratin</a>.',
