    instructions:
      "<ol><li>Preheat the oven to 400 F. Butter an 8x8-inch baking dish and set aside.</li><li>Steam the whole cauliflower until tender but not soggy (about 15 minutes). Cool and slice the cauliflower horizontally.</li><li>Heat the peanut oil in a saucepan over medium heat. Add the ginger, shallot, and garlic; saute for 3 to 4 minutes. Add the dry spices and saute until aromatic, about 3 minutes. Sprinkle in the flour and stir to cook, about 2 minutes. Whisk in the coconut milk and salt and cook at a simmer, stirring, about 3 to 5 minutes (until thickened).</li><li>Layer the cauliflower slices and curry cream in the prepared baking dish.</li><li>Sprinkle the cumin seeds and breadcrumbs over the cauliflower and curry cream. Drizzle the breadcrumbs with the melted butter. Bake for 25 to 30 minutes until golden brown and bubbling.</li><li>Sprinkle the finished dish with the minced cilantro and serve.</li></ol>",
